KW  - High-technology firms
KW  - Firm dynamics
AB  - This paper examines the impact of immigration policy frictions on technology-intensive firms by age cohort. The firm-level empirical evidence shows that H-1B policy restrictions on skilled immigrants directly affect the survival of young firms in technology-intensive sectors. We develop a novel general equilibrium model with firm entry and exit that mimics the policy frictions in the H-1B program. The model matches the age distribution of firms in high-technology sectors and shows that immigration policy reforms that increase the entry of younger firms induce greater exit of older, less productive firms, thereby increasing efficiency.
